  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>
    <refpurpose>Damon which executes script on devices.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>
      &basicapp;
      <arg choice="opt">
	<arg choice="plain"><option>--server <replaceable>server-name</replaceable></option></arg>
      </arg>
      <arg choice="opt">
	<arg choice="plain"><option>--port <replaceable>port</replaceable></option></arg>
      </arg>
      <arg choice="opt">
	<arg choice="plain"><option>--config <replaceable>config file</replaceable></option></arg>
      </arg>
      <arg choice="opt">
        <arg choice="plain"><option>--expand-path <replaceable>expand string</replaceable></option></arg>
      </arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id="description">
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command> enables execution of scripts on devices.
      It is different from
      <citerefentry><refentrytitle>rts2-scriptexec</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>
      that it runs as daemon. Scripts can be generated by execution programs
      with parameters.
    </para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1 id="options">
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    &optiongnu;

    <variablelist>
      &basicapplist;
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--server <replaceable class="parameter">server-name</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
	    Specify name of the host, which runs
	    <citerefentry><refentrytitle>rts2-centrald</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>.
	    This option is needed only for setups that use multiple computers.
	    Its default is localhost. Default will work for simple setups.
	  </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--port <replaceable class="parameter">port</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
	    Specify port of the
	    <citerefentry><refentrytitle>rts2-centrald</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>.
	    It defaults to RTS2 default port, specified during system
	    configuration. This value is usually 617.
	  </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--config <replaceable class="parameter">config-file</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Specify configuration file. defaults to <filename>/etc/rts2/rts2.ini</filename>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--expand-path <replaceable class="parameter">device name</replaceable></option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
	    Specify a device that will be used. The most common one is "C0", for
	    the main camera. Check
	    <citerefentry><refentrytitle>rts2-mon</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	    for a list of the devices that are present in your setup.
	  </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
